We have

\begin{align*}A - \lambda I = \left(\begin{array}{cc}
3 - \lambda & 1 \\ -4 & -1 - \lambda
\end{array}\right)\end{align*}

which has determinant

\begin{align*}\displaystyle{}(3 - \lambda)(-1 - \lambda) - (-4)(1) = \lambda^2 - 2 \lambda + 1.\end{align*}

Setting $\lambda^2 - 2 \lambda + 1 = 0$ we find $\lambda = 1$ as the
only eigenvalue.
